        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 1:23PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 123 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles south of Wolf Creek
to near Helena to near Boulder. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, Boulder, East Helena, Montana City, Wickes, York, Alhambra,
Spring Meadow Lake State Park, Corbin, Elkhorn State Park, Winston,
Clancy, Black Sandy State Park, and Jefferson City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
